 **Not gating Slice 0:** Go `fathom-integrity` erasure detection (no Go source in-tree; gitignored).
 
+### 4.1 Item 10 consequence — **multi-document extractor batches now require per-entity attribution** *(behavioral contract change)*
+
+Item 10 made ingest provenance caller-grounded. The mechanism (`resolve_provenance`)
+admits the model's `source_doc_id` echo **only as a selector** among the ids the
+caller supplied in the same batch, never as a value. That yields two different
+contracts depending on batch size, and the second one is **new work for callers**:
+
+| Batch | Echo required? | Behavior |
+|---|---|---|
+| **Single document** | No | Attribution is unambiguous. The echo is ignored outright and the caller's `ExtractDocument.source_doc_id` is used, even if the model omitted or altered the field. |
+| **Multiple documents** | **Yes, per entity AND per edge** | The echo must name one of the batch's caller-supplied ids. The caller's own copy of that string is then stored. An **absent or unrecognised** echo is a protocol violation and fails the ingest with `EngineError::Extractor`. |
+
+**Why the multi-document arm fails rather than defaults.** With several documents
+in flight the engine cannot know which one an entity came from. Every available
+fallback — first id in the batch, most recent, arbitrary — silently *mis-files*
+the row under a document whose erasure would then not remove it. That is exactly
+the un-erasable-row defect item 10 exists to close, so guessing would reintroduce
+the bug in a quieter form. **Failing loudly is the designed behavior and must not
+be relaxed.** `multidoc_batch_without_entity_echo_fails_loudly` and
+`multidoc_batch_with_foreign_echo_fails_loudly` pin it.
+
+**What callers must do.** An extractor that can attribute each element should set
+`source_doc_id` on every entity and every edge it returns. **An extractor that
+cannot attribute its output must submit single-document batches** — one
+`ExtractDocument` per `ingest_with_extractor` call — where attribution is
+unambiguous and no echo is needed. There is no third option, by construction.
+
+**How this was found (coverage note).** Item 10 shipped with single-document
+coverage only, which is precisely the branch that ignores the echo — so nothing
+exercised the arm that demands one, and the in-tree ELPS harness (which backfilled
+`source_doc_id` onto edges but never entities) broke on every multi-document
+batch. The general lesson for this slice: when a change introduces a
+**cardinality-dependent** contract, coverage of one cardinality proves nothing
+about the other.
+
+**Files carrying the requirement.** `src/python/eval/elps_live_harness.py` — both
+the runtime backfill and the LLM-facing system prompt + JSON schema, since a stub
+satisfying the contract is not evidence a live model will.
+
