codex
The Rust multidoc tests pass locally, but the Python conftest change breaks the documented/default pytest path used by the repository's agent verification loop unless an extra environment variable or prebuilt native extension is supplied. That makes the patch incorrect as-is for normal source-tree verification.

Review comment:

- [P2] Restore the default pytest path — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/orch-0.8.20-s5/src/python/tests/conftest.py:128-129
  In a normal source checkout that follows the documented setup (`pip install -e 'src/python[dev]'`), the editable binding is built without `test-hooks`; `scripts/agent-test.sh` then invokes `pytest` without setting `FATHOMDB_TESTS_ALLOW_REBUILD`, so this import-time raise makes the agent test/verify loop fail before collection. If auto-rebuild is unsafe by default, the dev-loop/setup path still needs to explicitly build/authorize hooks in an intended environment or skip consistently, otherwise clean editable installs with pytest are always red.
